FUSSELL, Respondent, v. CULLEN, Appellant. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. May 7, 1894.) Appeal from second district court. Action by George G. Fussell against Richard J. Cullen.

Argued before BOOKSTAVER, BISCHOFF, and PRYOR, JJ.

Niles & Johnson, for appellant. P. Q. Eckerson, for respondent.

No opinion. Ordered that the appeal be discontinued, without costs.
